# Project Rules

## Code Style

- TypeScript strict; no `any`
- Functional components; `const` arrow functions
- Tailwind for all styling; no custom CSS unless in `globals.css`
- Early returns for readability
- Event handlers prefixed with `handle`
- No semicolons

## Commits

- Format: `type(scope): description` (imperative mood, no period)
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `perf`

## Security

- Never log secrets or tokens
- Encrypt refresh/access tokens at rest
- Validate cron secret on background sync routes
- Rate-limit auth and sync endpoints

## Testing

- Run `pnpm lint`, `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm test` before marking work complete
- Pure logic in testable modules under `src/lib/**/aggregations.ts`
